
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `ibus` yek system vared kardane zaban-haye mokhtalef baraye Linux va UNIX mesl-e system-haye windows ast. Ba `ibus`, shoma mitoonid farsi, arabi, ya har zabane digeyi ro type konid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `ibus-setup` --> ⚙️ Baz kardane panjere-ye ayar-haye IBus.
    🔹 `ibus restart` --> 🔄 Baz-andazi (restart) kardane service `ibus`. Vaghti ke configuration-ha tagheer karde and, estefade mishavad.
    🔹 `ibus exit` --> 👋 Baste (exit) kardane `ibus`.
    🔹 `ibus read-cache` --> 🔄 Khondan-e dobare file-haye cache baraye tashkhis tagheerat dar engine-haye vared kardane zaban.
    🔹 `ibus engine <name>` --> ⌨️ Set kardane engine-e vared kardane zaban-e fa’al. Mesal: `ibus engine xkb:us`

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ ibus-setup

    🔹 In dastoor panjere-ye ayar-haye `ibus` ra baz mikonad, ke shoma mitavanid zaban-haye jadid ra ezafe konid va config-haye digar ra tagheer dahid.

    $ ibus restart

    🔹 In dastoor `ibus` ra baz-andazi mikonad, va in amr vaghti ke shoma zaban-haye jadid ezafe karde id ya configuration-haye `ibus` ra tagheer dade id mohem ast.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ ibus engine pinyin

    🔹 In dastoor engine-e `ibus` ra be `pinyin` tagheer midahad, ke shoma betavanid be zaban-e chineyi type konid. (agar `pinyin` engine install shode bashad).

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `ibus` command is an Intelligent Input Bus system for Linux and UNIX-like operating systems, similar to input methods in Windows. It allows you to type in various languages such as Persian, Arabic, or any other language.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `ibus-setup` --> ⚙️ Opens the IBus settings window.
    🔹 `ibus restart` --> 🔄 Restarts the `ibus` service. Used when configurations have been changed.
    🔹 `ibus exit` --> 👋 Exits `ibus`.
    🔹 `ibus read-cache` --> 🔄 Re-reads cache files to recognize changes in input method engines.
    🔹 `ibus engine <name>` --> ⌨️ Sets the active input method engine. Example: `ibus engine xkb:us`

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ ibus-setup

    🔹 This command opens the `ibus` settings window, where you can add new languages and modify other configurations.

    $ ibus restart

    🔹 This command restarts `ibus`, which is important after adding new languages or changing `ibus` configurations.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ ibus engine pinyin

    🔹 This command changes the `ibus` engine to `pinyin`, allowing you to type in Chinese (if the `pinyin` engine is installed).
